Citation.sTitle: Binary liquid liquid equilibrium in the systems containing monofunctional benzene derivates and 1,2-ethanediol
Citation.sAbstract: Binary liquid liquid equilibrium in the systems containing monofunctional benzene derivates (toluene or methoxybenzene or chlorobenzene or  acetophenone), and 1,2-ethanediol was measured by the volumetric method in the temperature range 283 333 K. It was found that solubilities of  the selected monofunctional benzene derivates at ambient temperature were approximately 200 times higher than that in water. The experimental  data were correlated by the NRTL equation.
